To display an SVG image in React JSX, you can use the `<svg>` element to define the image and its properties, such as height and width. You can then use the `<image>` element to reference the SVG file and render it on the page. Here is an example JSX code:

```
import React from 'react';

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div>
      <svg height="100" width="100">
        <image href="path/to/image.svg" height="100" width="100" />
      </svg>
    </div>
  );
}

export default MyComponent;
```

In this example, the `image` element references the SVG file using the `href` attribute, and sets its height and width to match the `svg` element's height and width. The SVG file will be rendered inside the `svg` element on the page.

